{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"bf424003-4e7b-486d-a2e7-43ab54bc80e8","content":"The issue is the **file compilation order** in the `.fsproj`. In F#, files can only reference types/modules from files listed **above** them. `Services.fs` depends on `Domain.fs`, but it's listed first.\n\nFixing the order to: `Domain.fs` → `Services.fs` → `Program.fs`.","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"tooluse_o2V0SAHmTPns7UEPzjcJBm","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-7d8ec1b0ce6b4504a685d091fa7e71bc/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj","old_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />","new_str":"    <Compile Include=\"Domain.fs\" />\n    <Compile Include=\"Services.fs\" />"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-7d8ec1b0ce6b4504a685d091fa7e71bc/fsharp/BrokenOrder/BrokenOrder.fsproj."}],"interactionId":"597d0544-9fff-4ad4-a751-b13291f3f0d8","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The issue is clear. In F#, file order matters — files can only reference modules/types defined in files listed *before* them in the `.fsproj`. \n\nCurrently the order is:\n1. Services.fs — depends on Domain.fs (opens BrokenOrder.Domain)\n2. Domain.fs — defines the types\n3. Program.fs — depends on both\n\nServices.fs is listed before Domain.fs, but Services.fs depends on Domain.fs. The fix is to reorder so Domain.fs comes first.\n\nCorrect order: Domain.fs → Services.fs → Program.fs","outputTokens":400,"requestId":"1920:18EC0:12F4BE9:15536F8:6A066F07"},"id":"3859370f-2ab5-44ac-b055-301afe1f67c6","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:55:42.812Z","parentId":"b75d4420-6fb6-4344-91bd-ca1cf819a1c4"}
